column10: The division Server Build Services (SBS) builds/install/configure logical servers (ESX/VMware) and physical machines (Windows Unix/Linux) based on a request (e.g. RfS). The service starts with the racking cabling (e.g. Power LAN SAN IBR) adding necessary HW parts like local disks RAM HBA/NIC-cards followed by the software-installation (OS DB MW Tools) based on a demand/implementation design. SBS is performing also the service-decommissioning and physical/logical relocation of servers/machine. SBS supports also Transitions & Transformations (T&T) and the Workload Migration Service (WMS) team due to its migration projects.

column10: Guys work on site in reading with client and have a unique skillset in that they have intimate knowledge of the SHell and GB Nrtworking evnirnoment. John created a (chargeable) feasibility study which allowed us be downseleted to proceed to contract on the $1.2M APO deal. Without him we will struggle to get to contract and certainly lose significant revenue in Q. Cisco CSPC collector (Shell inventory/software/vulnerability reporting) The collector is of paramount important to Shell to report on the network landscape in ex-BG locations for maintenance contract renewal end of life hardware and software vulnerabilities this could account for a work stream for IBM to replace a large amount of equipment. (Completion end of May) 2) Ironport End of Life Replacing the Cisco Ironports in the ex-BG locations with the Shell standard Zscaler solution if not complete by end of June Shell will be faced with a $350k bill and a ah-hoc internet solution with risk. 3) Shell CUBE infrastructure Project to install Shell infrastructure for the CUBE environments in Trinidad Bolivia Tunisia and Brisbane. (End of June completion) 4) BG DC consolidation Shell is currently looking at remediating Thames and Dallas DC also to resize UK1 DC. (Ongoing) 5) Shell/BG network interconnect for Chinchiilla (backup) Project to implement link into Chinchilla for backup Shell access. (end of June completion) 6) Transition of Tunisia assets to APO IBM tendered project (Dec’17 completion date) -  This is one of the new Divestment opportunity where Shell is divesting its one of the refinery to APO.. IBM team has been shortlisted for this project and one of the key reason for IBM getting shortlisted is the knowledge and skills demonstrated by John and Darren during the feasibility study which has compelled the project in IBM favour.
